.Dd February 25, 2026
.Dt MINIWEB 1
.Os OpenBSD
.Sh NAME
.Nm miniweb
.Nd OpenBSD-native C99 HTTP server with modular architecture
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl hv
.Op Fl b Ar address
.Op Fl c Ar connections
.Op Fl f Ar file
.Op Fl l Ar logfile
.Op Fl p Ar port
.Op Fl t Ar threads
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a lightweight HTTP server written in C99 for OpenBSD.
It exposes a system dashboard and JSON APIs for metrics, networking
diagnostics, manual page browsing, and package management.
.Pp
The runtime uses a single
.Xr kqueue 2
dispatcher thread and a configurable worker-thread pool.
All modules are registered through a central attach API and maintain
their own ring buffer caches, updated by a global heartbeat scheduler.
.Pp
.Nm
does not implement TLS directly.
Run it behind
.Xr relayd 8
for TLS termination.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl b Ar address
Bind to an IPv4 address.
Default is
.Cm 127.0.0.1 .
.It Fl c Ar connections
Maximum concurrent connections.
Clamped to the compile-time limit of
.Cm 4096 .
Default is
.Cm 1280 .
.It Fl f Ar file
Load configuration from
.Ar file .
A parse error in an explicitly supplied file is fatal.
.It Fl h
Print usage and exit.
.It Fl l Ar logfile
Append log output to
.Ar logfile
instead of stderr.
.It Fl p Ar port
TCP listen port.
Default is
.Cm 9001 .
.It Fl t Ar threads
Worker thread count.
Clamped to the range 1\(en32.
Default is
.Cm 4 .
.It Fl v
Enable verbose logging.
Equivalent to setting
.Cm verbose yes
in the configuration file.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION FILE
On startup
.Nm
searches for a configuration file in the following order (first file found
wins):
.Pp
.Bl -enum -compact
.It
Explicit path from the
.Fl f
flag.
.It
.Pa ./miniweb.conf
.It
.Pa $HOME/.miniweb.conf
.It
.Pa /etc/miniweb.conf
.El
.Pp
If no file is found, compiled-in defaults are used and startup continues
normally.
CLI flags always override file values.
.Pp
The file format is one directive per line:
.Pp
.Dl key value
.Pp
Keys are case-insensitive.
Lines beginning with
.Ql #
and blank lines are ignored.
.Pp
Supported keys:
.Bl -tag -width "mandoc_timeout"
.It Cm port
TCP listen port.
Default:
.Cm 9001 .
.It Cm bind , bind_addr
IPv4 address to bind to.
Default:
.Cm 127.0.0.1 .
Use
.Cm 0.0.0.0
to listen on all interfaces.
.It Cm threads
Worker thread count.
Clamped to 1\(en32.
Default:
.Cm 4 .
.It Cm max_conns
Maximum concurrent connections.
Default:
.Cm 1280 .
.It Cm conn_timeout
Idle connection timeout in seconds.
Default:
.Cm 30 .
.It Cm max_req_size
Maximum HTTP request size in bytes.
Must not exceed the compile-time limit of
.Cm 16384 .
Default:
.Cm 16384 .
.It Cm mandoc_timeout
Timeout for
.Xr mandoc 1
subprocess invocations, in seconds.
Default:
.Cm 10 .
.It Cm static_dir
Path to the static assets directory.
Default:
.Pa static .
.It Cm templates_dir
Path to the HTML templates directory.
Default:
.Pa templates .
.It Cm mandoc_path
Path to the
.Xr mandoc 1
binary.
Default:
.Pa /usr/bin/mandoc .
.It Cm trusted_proxy
IPv4 address of a reverse proxy whose
.Dv X-Forwarded-For ,
.Dv X-Forwarded-Proto ,
and
.Dv X-Real-IP
headers are honoured.
Default:
.Cm 127.0.0.1 .
.It Cm verbose
Enable verbose logging.
Accepted values:
.Cm yes , no , true , false , 1 , 0 .
Default:
.Cm no .
.It Cm log_file
Log file path.
Empty or absent means stderr.
.El
.Sh RUNTIME ARCHITECTURE
.Nm
uses a two-tier threading model.
.Pp
The
.Em dispatcher thread
(main) owns the
.Xr kqueue 2
file descriptor, runs the accept loop, and enqueues ready connections into a
ring-buffer work queue.
It never calls a route handler.
.Pp
The
.Em worker pool
(N threads, configurable via
.Fl t )
dequeues connections, reads the full HTTP request, parses the request line
and headers, dispatches the matching route handler, and either closes the
socket or re-arms it for keep-alive.
.Pp
Compile-time hard limits:
.Bl -tag -width "REQUEST_BUFFER_SIZE"
.It Dv MAX_EVENTS
256 \(em
.Xr kevent 2
batch size per iteration.
.It Dv MAX_CONNECTIONS
4096 \(em connection pool size.
.It Dv THREAD_POOL_SIZE
32 \(em maximum worker threads.
.It Dv REQUEST_BUFFER_SIZE
16384 \(em per-connection receive buffer.
.It Dv LISTEN_BACKLOG
1024 \(em
.Xr listen 2
backlog.
.It Dv QUEUE_CAPACITY
4096 \(em work queue ring-buffer capacity.
.It Dv MAX_KEEPALIVE_REQUESTS
64 \(em requests per keep-alive connection.
.El
.Sh KQUEUE DISPATCHER
The listening socket is registered with
.Dv EVFILT_READ | EV_CLEAR
so that the backlog counter resets after every
.Xr kevent 2
return.
.Pp
Client sockets are registered with
.Dv EV_ADD | EV_DISPATCH .
.Dv EV_DISPATCH
automatically disables the event after the first delivery, eliminating the
race where multiple workers could receive the same file descriptor.
.Pp
Each main-loop iteration uses a 1-second timeout so that idle connection
sweeping runs at least once per second regardless of traffic.
The sweep closes connections whose
.Dv last_activity
timestamp is older than
.Cm conn_timeout .
.Pp
When the OS file descriptor table is full
.Pq Dv EMFILE / ENFILE ,
the dispatcher closes a reserved
.Pa /dev/null
spare descriptor, accepts and immediately drops one pending client to prevent
the listen socket from busy-looping, then reopens the spare.
.Pp
The
.Dv udata
pointer in each
.Xr kevent 2
structure is validated against a per-file-descriptor generation counter before
dispatching.
Stale pointers from recycled descriptors are silently ignored.
.Sh WORKER POOL AND WORK QUEUE
Workers are identical POSIX threads sharing a single ring-buffer work queue
protected by a mutex and a condition variable.
.Pp
The dispatcher enqueues connections non-blocking; if the queue is full the
connection is dropped with a
.Cm 503
response.
Workers block on
.Fn pthread_cond_wait
until a connection is available or the server shuts down.
.Pp
Within a worker, the read loop accumulates data from the non-blocking socket
until the HTTP header terminator
.Pq Dv \er\en\er\en
is found.
If
.Dv EAGAIN
is returned before headers are complete, the
.Xr kqueue 2
event is re-enabled with
.Dv EV_ENABLE
and the worker returns without closing the connection.
.Pp
Keep-alive connections are re-armed after each request.
A connection is closed unconditionally after
.Dv MAX_KEEPALIVE_REQUESTS
(64) requests on the same socket.
.Sh CONNECTION POOL
The connection pool is a flat array of
.Vt connection_t
structs indexed by file descriptor.
Allocation and deallocation are O(1) via a LIFO free-stack.
Each slot carries the client socket, peer address, receive buffer,
activity timestamps, request count, and a generation counter.
The generation counter allows the dispatcher to detect stale
.Xr kevent 2
.Dv udata
pointers: if the counter in the event does not match the current counter for
that file descriptor, the event is a stale reference to a recycled socket and
is ignored.
.Sh HTTP LAYER
.Ss Response pool
.Fn http_response_create
allocates a response object from a per-thread shard of a static response pool
(16 shards, 1024 slots each) to avoid a
.Xr malloc 3
call on every request.
If the pool is exhausted it falls back to
.Xr calloc 3 .
.Ss Serialisation
.Fn http_response_send
serialises the status line, standard headers
.Pq Content-Type , Content-Length , Connection , Server ,
optional custom headers, and the body using a single
.Xr writev 2
call when a body is present, or
.Xr write 2
for header-only responses.
Write retries handle
.Dv EAGAIN / EWOULDBLOCK
on non-blocking sockets.
.Ss Subprocess execution
.Fn safe_popen_read_argv
forks, redirects stdout to a pipe, redirects stderr to
.Pa /dev/null ,
and reads up to
.Ar max_size
bytes with a wall-clock timeout enforced by
.Xr poll 2 .
On timeout the child is sent
.Dv SIGKILL
before
.Xr waitpid 2 .
.Sh ROUTING AND MODULES
Routing is fully modular through the module attach API.
.Fn init_routes
in
.Pa src/router/url_registry.c
builds a
.Vt miniweb_module
list and lets each enabled module attach its own endpoints through
.Fn router_register .
.Pp
Routes are stored in two tables:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Exact routes: flat array of
.Vt struct route
(up to
.Dv MAX_ROUTES
= 32).
.It
Prefix routes: array of
.Vt struct prefix_route
(up to 16) for dynamic paths like
.Pa /man/* ,
.Pa /static/* ,
and
.Pa /api/packages/* .
.El
.Pp
.Fn route_match
resolves a handler in two passes:
.Bl -enum
.It
Exact match: linear scan comparing method and path strings.
.It
Prefix match: checks prefix routes with optional minimum slash requirements.
.El
.Pp
When a path exists but the method doesn't match, a
.Cm 405 Method Not Allowed
response is sent with an
.Dv Allow
header built by
.Fn route_allow_methods .
Unknown paths receive
.Cm 404 Not Found .
.Sh MODULE SYSTEM
Modules are registered through
.Fn miniweb_module_attach_enabled
in
.Pa src/router/module_attach.c .
Each module provides:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Va name :
Module identifier.
.It
.Fn init :
Optional initialization callback.
.It
.Fn attach_routes :
Registers endpoints with the router.
.It
.Fn shutdown :
Optional cleanup callback.
.It
.Va enabled_by_default :
Flag for automatic enabling.
.El
.Pp
All built-in modules (views, metrics, networking, man, packages) are attached
at startup through this contract.
.Sh CACHING ARCHITECTURE
.Nm
employs multiple caching layers for optimal performance.
.Ss Ring buffer caches (per-module)
.Bl -column "Module" "Cache Type" "Size" "TTL" "Description" -offset indent
.It Em Module Ta Em Cache Type Ta Em Size Ta Em TTL Ta Em Description
.It Metrics Ta Ring buffer Ta 1MB Ta 1s Ta Samples system metrics every second.
.It Networking Ta Ring buffer Ta 1MB Ta 1s Ta Samples network stats every second.
.It Packages Ta Ring buffer Ta 2MB Ta 30s Ta Caches all package queries (search, info, files, list, which).
.It Man pages Ta Sharded render cache Ta 16×128 slots Ta 600s Ta Caches rendered man page content.
.El
.Ss Static file cache
.Pa src/http/response.c
implements a sharded in-memory file cache:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
16 independent shards, each with 32 slots.
.It
Files up to 256 KiB are cached.
.It
Two-stage admission policy (requires 2 requests before caching).
.It
Token bucket rate limiting (8 inserts/sec per shard).
.It
120-second TTL with LRU eviction.
.El
.Ss Template cache
.Pa src/render/template_render.c
preloads all HTML templates at startup and refreshes them every 60 seconds.
.Ss Hot view cache
.Pa src/router/route_table.c
caches rendered HTML for top-level pages
.Pq Pa / , /docs , /networking , /packages , /apiroot
with a 10-second TTL.
.Pp
All ring buffer caches track hit/miss ratios and log them periodically.
.Sh HEARTBEAT SCHEDULER
.Pa src/core/heartbeat.c
provides a generic periodic task scheduler.
Up to
.Dv HB_MAX_TASKS
(32) named tasks can be registered with
.Fn heartbeat_register .
Each task specifies a callback, an opaque context pointer, a period in
seconds, and an initial delay.
.Pp
.Fn heartbeat_register
returns:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Dv HB_REGISTER_INSERTED
(1) on success.
.It
.Dv HB_REGISTER_DUPLICATE
(0) for a duplicate name (non-fatal).
.It
.Dv HB_REGISTER_ERROR
(-1) on invalid input or a full table.
.El
.Pp
.Fn heartbeat_start
spawns a single background thread that fires due tasks and tracks overrun
counts per task.
.Fn heartbeat_shutdown Ar drain
stops the scheduler; when
.Ar drain
is non-zero, every active task is executed one final time before the thread
exits.
.Pp
Registered heartbeat tasks:
.Bl -column "Task Name" "Period" "Module" "Purpose" -offset indent
.It Em Task Name Ta Em Period Ta Em Module Ta Em Purpose
.It Dq metrics.sample Ta 1s Ta Metrics Ta Sample system metrics.
.It Dq networking.sample Ta 1s Ta Networking Ta Sample network stats.
.It Dq packages.snapshot Ta 60s Ta Packages Ta Refresh package list cache.
.It Dq man.cache_cleanup Ta 60s Ta Man pages Ta Clean expired cache entries.
.El
.Sh MODULES
.Ss Views module
.Pq Pa src/router/route_table.c
Provides the template-rendered HTML dashboard pages:
.Pa / , /docs , /networking , /packages , /apiroot , /favicon.ico , /static/*
Uses the hot view cache (10s TTL) for top-level pages.
.Ss Metrics module
.Pq Pa src/modules/metrics/
Provides
.Pa /api/metrics
with comprehensive system metrics.
.Pp
Collection methods:
.Xr sysctl 3
.Pq Dv KERN_CPTIME , VM_UVMEXP , KERN_BOOTTIME , KERN_PROC_ALL ,
.Xr swapctl 2 ,
.Xr getloadavg 3 ,
.Xr uname 3 ,
.Xr getmntinfo 3 .
.Pp
Caching: 1MB ring buffer with 1-second samples, 120-sample history window,
heartbeat-driven updates.
.Ss Networking module
.Pq Pa src/modules/networking/
Provides
.Pa /api/networking
with network diagnostics.
.Pp
Collection methods:
.Xr sysctl 3
.Pq Dv NET_RT_DUMP ,
parsing of
.Pa /etc/resolv.conf ,
.Xr getifaddrs 3
with
.Vt if_data .
.Pp
Caching: 1MB ring buffer with 1-second samples, pre-built JSON snapshot updated
every second.
.Ss Man pages module
.Pq Pa src/modules/man/
Provides rendered man pages and JSON API.
.Pp
Endpoints:
.Pa /man/{area}/{section}/{page}[.{html|txt|md|pdf|ps}] ,
.Pa /api/man/sections ,
.Pa /api/man/pages?section={s}&area={a} ,
.Pa /api/man/search?q={query} ,
.Pa /api/man/resolve?name={n}&section={s} .
.Pp
Rendering: Forks
.Xr mandoc 1
with configurable timeout (default 10s), supports HTML, text, markdown, PDF,
and PostScript output.
.Pp
Caching: Sharded render cache (16 shards × 128 slots = 2048 cached pages) with
600-second TTL, plus filesystem cache under
.Pa {static_dir}/man/ .
.Ss Packages module
.Pq Pa src/modules/packages/
Provides package management API via
.Xr pkg_info 1 .
.Pp
Endpoints:
.Pa /api/packages/search?q={query} ,
.Pa /api/packages/info?name={pkg} ,
.Pa /api/packages/which?path={file} ,
.Pa /api/packages/files?name={pkg} ,
.Pa /api/packages/list .
.Pp
Caching: 2MB ring buffer with 30-second TTL, stores all query types, hit/miss
tracking, on-demand population (no heartbeat needed).
.Sh STORAGE LAYER
.Pa src/storage/
contains stub implementations of a planned SQLite3 service layer.
The interfaces are defined but not yet implemented:
.Fn mw_db_open ,
.Fn mw_db_close ,
.Fn mw_db_exec_schema ,
.Fn mw_db_migrate ,
.Fn mw_tx_begin ,
.Fn mw_tx_commit ,
.Fn mw_tx_rollback ,
.Fn mw_stmt_prepare ,
.Fn mw_bind_text ,
.Fn mw_bind_int64 ,
.Fn mw_bind_null ,
.Fn mw_stmt_step ,
.Fn mw_stmt_finalize .
.Pp
All stub functions currently return
.Dv -1
(unimplemented).
The headers are stable and intended for Phase 5 of the modularity roadmap.
.Sh OPENBSD SECURITY HARDENING
After worker threads are started,
.Fn apply_openbsd_security
restricts the process with
.Xr unveil 2
and
.Xr pledge 2 .
.Pp
.Xr unveil 2
grants access only to:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Cm templates_dir
(read),
.Cm static_dir
(read/write/create).
.It
.Pa /usr/share/man , /usr/local/man , /usr/X11R6/man
(read).
.It
.Cm mandoc_path ,
.Pa /usr/bin/man , /usr/bin/apropos , /usr/sbin/pkg_info
(execute).
.It
.Pa /bin/sh
(execute for fallback popen).
.It
.Pa /var/db/pkg
(read).
.It
.Pa /etc/passwd , /etc/group
(read for process username resolution).
.It
.Pa /etc/resolv.conf
(read).
.It
.Pa /dev/null
(read/write).
.El
.Pp
.Xr pledge 2
promises:
.Dl stdio rpath wpath cpath inet route proc exec vminfo ps getpw
.Pp
On non-OpenBSD platforms both calls are compiled out.
.Sh LOGGING
.Pa src/core/log.c
provides a thread-safe, mutex-protected logger.
Log lines are formatted as:
.Dl [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS] [LEVEL] message
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width "log_errno()"
.It Fn log_init
Opens the log file (appending) or defaults to stderr.
.It Fn log_close
Flushes and closes the log file.
.It Fn log_info , log_error
Always emitted.
.It Fn log_debug
Emitted only in verbose mode.
.It Fn log_errno
Calls
.Fn log_error
with
.Xr strerror 3
of the current
.Va errno .
.El
